      "work_around": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "value": "Mitigation for this issue is to skip loading the affected module \"vmxnet3\" onto the system until the fix is available, this can be done by a blacklist mechanism which will ensure the driver is not loaded at the boot time.\n~~~\nHow do I blacklist a kernel module to prevent it from loading automatically?\nhttps://access.redhat.com/solutions/41278 \n~~~"
